444. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Ovid MEDLINE(R) <2020>
ID  - 32960105
T1  - Nutritional and dietary aspects in polycystic ovary syndrome: insights into the biology of nutritional interventions.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/09513590.2020.1822797
A1  - Neves, Luisa Pinheiro Pimenta
A1  - Marcondes, Rodrigo Rodrigues
A1  - Maffazioli, Giovana De Nardo
A1  - Simoes, Ricardo Santos
A1  - Maciel, Gustavo Arantes Rosa
A1  - Soares, Jose Maria Jr
A1  - Baracat, Edmund Chada
Y1  - 2020//
Y2  - 20200922//
N2  - Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS) is a complex endocrine disorder, which affects 5-17% of reproductive age women and is often associated with obesity and metabolic impairment. Common treatment strategies are based on exercise, diet and nutrient supplementation since PCOS is often linked with obesity and metabolic impairment. Studies have recommended that nutrition is a key factor in the health maintenance of women with PCOS, however, little is known about the subject in the context of such a disease. This narrative review aims to identify dietary and nutritional aspects of PCOS and discuss the role of nutrients in management of polycystic ovary syndrome in view of clinical trials.
