710. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Ovid MEDLINE(R) <2018>
ID  - 29544638
T1  - Developmental Programming of Ovarian Functions and Dysfunctions.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/bs.vh.2018.01.017
A1  - Puttabyatappa, Muraly
A1  - Padmanabhan, Vasantha
Y1  - 2018//
Y2  - 20180222//
N2  - The pathophysiological mechanisms underlying the origin of several ovarian pathologies remain unclear. In addition to the genetic basis, developmental insults are gaining attention as a basis for the origin of these pathologies. Such early insults include maternal over or under nutrition, stress, and exposure to environmental chemicals. This chapter reviews the development and physiological function of the ovary, the known ovarian pathologies, the developmental check points of ovarian differentiation impacted by developmental insults, the role played by steroidal and metabolic factors as mediaries, the epigenetic mechanisms via which these mediaries induce their effects, and the knowledge gaps for targeting future studies to ultimately aid in the development of improved treatments. Copyright © 2018 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
